Class Card

java.lang.Object
src.Card
public class Card extends Object
This program defines a Card class representing a playing card with its rank and suit. A card can also be in an empty, undefined state.

    • compare

      public static int compare(Card firstCard, Card secondCard)
      Compares two cards by rank and suit. The comparison is done using the respective order of the rank and suit in their arrays. Ties are determined by the ordering of Suits.
      Parameters:
      firstCard - the first card to compare
      secondCard - the second card to compare
      Returns:
      a negative number when firstCard invalid input: '<' secondCard, zero if equal, positive if firstCard > secondCard.
